  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the sliced galangal and cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until it starts to soften, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional minute.",
    "Add the lamb shoulder and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, paprika, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Pour in the chicken broth and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, until the lamb is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.",
    "Serve the stew hot, garnished with fresh herbs if desired."
